20/08/2007
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Bavarian Prime Minister Edmund Stoiber said on Sunday (August 19th) that he hopes Croatia could complete all procedures and become a member of the EU in 2009. 
Meeting with Croatian Prime Minister Ivo Sanader, Stoiber said that Croatia had met all Union requirements and is much farther along than fellow aspirant Turkey. 
For his part, Sanader said Croatia is turning from a consumer to a provider of services. 
(Vjesnik, Vecernji list - 20/08/07; Index.hr; Javno.com, Makfax - 19/08/07)
